<br>
Rodrick is best done late in the AM when all the n00bs are done with the fort.  Just park yourself in front of the tower that he spawns in and hide/sneak/AFK.  Have no idea on spawn times, took me less then an hour.  Was very green to 60, took about 5 seconds to kill.<br>
<br>
Murdrick is best done with a druid and a monk.  Druid goes into cave, without wolf form on, and harmonies.  Monk solo pulls. Murdrick is blue at 60 and very easy to kill with the 3 classes mentioned above.<br>
<br>
Berradin is cake.<br>
<br>
Peffin was my bane, as I had a few problems with her spawn.  I recommend waiting until a server reset as most groups do not kill the giant spawns, and you can have literally dozens of giants spawned at the fire.  Peffin is blue, and was easily killed by a cleric/monk/rogue.  Remember, no damage shields for this, the fire-side giants will summon.<br>
<br>
Doligun and the giants are cake.  Cleric/monk/paladin/rogue/warrior had no problems at all.  I would recommend cleric/warrior/etc for certain.<br>
<br>
Juliah was also just as easy.  Had over-kill with cleric/shaman/warrior/paladin/rogue/rogue.  Again cleric/warrior is recommended.  A decent Shadowknight/Paladin could tank just as well though.<br>
<br>
10 war is great.  Make sure you have 35+  of your guildmates.  We seem to always have 39.  Anything more then 45 would just be lag.  Remind everyone that any melee can tank the giants if they are slowed.  Go for the warlords first.  Can't think of much more, it's a fun event and well worth the time to get to it. <br>
<br>
I was max ally to Coldian and the Dain when I earned my 10 ring.  During the first 8 rings I was completely maxed negative faction with Coldian/Dain.  For 9 ring I was still KoS when getting the box, but by the time I was ready to hand it in I was kindly.  By 10 ring I was max ally.  <br>
<br>
Siyni<br>
